'''Order of Admiral Yi Sun-Shin''' ({{korean|context=north|hangul=이순신장군훈장}}) is an award that is named after famous Korean naval leader [[Yi Sun-sin]],{{citation needed|date=April 2016}} and it was given to [[Korean People's Navy]] personnel of [[North Korea]] at least during the [[Korean War]].<ref name="SinoNK_2016"/>
There are two grades of the award.<ref name="medals_org">{{cite web|url=http://www.medals.org.uk/north-korea/north-korea007.htm|title=ODM of North Korea: Order of Admiral Li Sun Sin|date=8 March 2012|access-date=16 April 2016}}</ref> Order of Admiral Yi Sun-Shin First Class ({{lang|ko|이순신장군훈장 제1급}}), and Order of Admiral Yi Sun-Shin Second Class ({{lang|ko|이순신장군훈장 제2급}}).
==History==
The second class of this award was given 22 times during Korean War. However, the first class award was not given during the war.<ref name="SinoNK_2016">{{cite web|url=http://sinonk.com/2016/01/08/chests-full-of-brass-a-dprk-political-history-in-orders-medals-prizes-and-titles/|title=Chests Full of Brass: A DPRK Political History in Orders, Medals, Prizes, and Titles |date=8 January 2016|last=Weiser |first=Martin |access-date=16 April 2016}}</ref>
The award has been assumed to have been discontinued at an unknown date. It is assumed from photographic evidence that the award was given for some years after the war, as an award with serial number 113 exists.<ref name="SinoNK_2016"/>
